r, backing vocals\n*Jerry Dixon \u2013 bass, backing vocals\n*'''Danny Wagner \u2013 drums''' {{small|(temporary)}}\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|January \u2013 August 2000\n|\n*Jani Lane \u2013 vocals, acoustic guitar, keyboards\n*'''[[Keri Kelli]] \u2013 lead guitar''' {{small|(temporary)}}\n*Erik Turner \u2013 rhythm guitar, backing vocals\n*Jerry Dixon \u2013 bass, backing vocals\n*'''[[Mike Fasano (musician)|Mike Fasano]] \u2013 drums, percussion'''\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Late 2000 \u2013 April 2003\n|\n*Jani Lane \u2013 vocals, acoustic guitar, keyboards\n*'''[[Billy Morris (guitarist)|Billy Morris]] \u2013 lead guitar, backing vocals'''\n*Erik Turner \u2013 rhythm guitar, backing vocals\n*Jerry Dixon \u2013 bass, backing vocals\n*Mike Fasano \u2013 drums, percussion\n|\n*''[[Under the Influence (Warrant album)|Under the Influence]]'' (2001)\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|April 2003 \u2013 January 2004\n|\n*Jani Lane \u2013 vocals, acoustic guitar, keyboards\n*Billy Morris \u2013 lead guitar, backing vocals\n*Erik Turner \u2013 rhythm guitar, backing vocals\n*Jerry Dixon \u2013 bass, backing vocals\n*'''Kevin Phares \u2013 drums, percussion'''\n|rowspan=\"2\"|none\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|February \u2013 March 2004\n|\n*'''[[Jaime St. James]] \u2013 lead vocals'''\n*'''Joey Allen \u2013 lead guitar, backing vocals'''\n*Erik Turner \u2013 rhythm guitar, backing vocals\n*Jerry Dixon \u2013 bass, backing vocals\n*'''Mike Fasano \u2013 drums, percussion'''\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|March 2004 \u2013 January 2008\n|\n*Jaime St. James \u2013 lead vocals\n*Joey Allen \u2013 lead guitar, backing vocals\n*Erik Turner \u2013 rhythm guitar, backing vocals\n*Jerry Dixon \u2013 bass, backing vocals\n*'''Steven Sweet \u2013 drums, percussion, backing vocals'''\n|\n*''[[Born Again (Warrant album)|Born Again]]'' (2006)\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|January \u2013 September 2008\n|\n*'''Jani Lane \u2013 lead vocals, acoustic guitar'''\n*Joey Allen \u2013 lead guitar, backing vocals\n*Erik Turner \u2013 rhythm guitar, backing vocals\n*Jerry Dixon \u2013 bass, backing vocals\n*Steven Sweet \u2013 drums, percussion, backing vocals\n|none\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|September 2008 \u2013 present\n|\n*'''Robert Mason \u2013 vocals, acoustic guitar, harmonica'''\n*Joey Allen \u2013 lead guitar, backing vocals\n*Erik Turner \u2013 rhythm guitar, backing vocals\n*Jerry Dixon \u2013 bass, backing vocals\n*Steven Sweet \u2013 drums, percussion, backing vocals\n|\n*''[[Rockaholic]]'' (2011)\n*''[[Louder Harder Faster]]'' (2017)\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.warrantrocks.com/ Warrant official website]\n\n{{Warrant}}\n\n[[Category:Warrant (American band) members|*]]\n[[Category:Lists of members by band|Warrant]]\n", "text_old": "[[Warrant (American band)|Warrant]] is an American [[glam metal]] band from [[Hollywood]], [[California]]. Formed in 1984, the group originally included vocalist and acoustic guitarist [[Adam Shore]], lead guitarist [[Josh Lewis (guitarist)|Josh Lewis]], rhythm guitarist [[Erik Turner]], bassist Chris Vincent and drummer Max Asher, although Vincent was replaced after only a few months by [[Jerry Dixon (musician)|Jerry Dixon]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/jerry-dixon-mn0000327495/biography |title=Jerry Dixon: Biography & History |last=Harris |first=Craig |website=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=July 26, 2018 }}</ref> Shore and Asher left in September 1986, with Turner bringing in [[Jani Lane]] and [[Steven Sweet]] from the group Plain Jane as their replacements.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.loudmag.com.au/features/jani-lane-gone-soon/ |title=Jani Lane: Gone Too Soon |last=Giffin |first=Brian |work=Loud Magazine |date=August 12, 2011 |accessdate=July 26, 2018 }}</ref> The following March, [[Joey Allen]] replaced Lewis.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.vqpr.com/warrantpress-body.htm |title=\"Warrant\" Announces New Band Line-Up For 2004 |publisher=V.Q. Promotions |date=February 16, 2004 |accessdate=July 26, 2018 }}</ref> Warrant released its debut album ''[[Dirty Rotten Filthy Stinking Rich]]'' in 1989, which was followed by ''[[Cherry Pie (album)|Cherry Pie]]'' the following year and ''[[Dog Eat Dog (Warrant album)|Dog Eat Dog]]'' in 1992.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/warrant-mn0000193963/biography |title=Warrant: Biography & History |last=Erlewine |first=Stephen Thomas |author-link=Stephen Thomas Erlewine |website=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=July 26, 2018 }}</ref> Lane briefly left Warrant in March 1993 to start a solo career, but within 18 months had returned to the band.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/warrant-guitarist-talks-about-jani-lane-s-passing/ |title=Warrant Guitarist Talks About Jani Lane's Passing |website=[[Blabbermouth.net]] |date=August 29, 2011 |accessdate=July 26, 2018 }}</ref>\n\nPrior to Lane's return, Allen also left in May 1994, followed by Sweet the following month; later in the year, they were replaced by [[Kingdom Come (band)|Kingdom Come]]'s [[Rick Steier]] and [[James Kottak]], respectively.<ref name=\"underrated\">{{cite web |url=http://www.rawrootsrock.com.au/?os_articles=jani-lane-an-under-rated-rock-legend |title=Jani Lane \u2013 An under-rated Rock Legend |website=Raw Roots Rock |date=September 5, 2012 |accessdate=July 26, 2018 }}</ref> Kottak only remained for two years, with Bobby Borg taking his place after the release and touring of ''[[Ultraphobic]]''.<ref name=\"underrated\"/> Borg left in 1997 and was replaced on tour by Vik Foxx and later Danny Wagner, the latter of whom had previously played keyboards for the group.<ref name=\"AOR\">{{cite web |url=http://www.aordreamer.com/show_bios.php?artist_id=318 |title=Warrant: \"Down Boys\" |website=AORDreamer.com |accessdate=July 26, 2018 }}</ref> Steier and Wagner both subsequently left the band in early 2000.<ref name=\"AOR\"/> Replacing Steier with [[Billy Morris (guitarist)|Billy Morris]] and Wagner with [[Mike Fasano]], Warrant released ''[[Under the Influence (Warrant album)|Under the Influence]]'', an album of [[cover version]]s, in 2001.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sleazeroxx.com/interviews/billy-morris-of-tuff-interview-part-2-of-3/ |title=Billy Morris of Tuff Interview (Part 2 of 3) |last=Troyan |first=Greg |website=Sleaze Roxx |date=October 9, 2015 |accessdate=July 26, 2018 }}</ref> On April 2, 2003, Fasano was fired from the band by Lane, with Kevin Phares of the vocalist's solo band taking his place.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://bravewords.com/news/warrant-drummer-released |title=Warrant - Drummer Released! |work=[[Brave Words & Bloody Knuckles]] |date=April 3, 2003 |accessdate=July 26, 2018 }}</ref>\n\nLane left Warrant for a second time in January 2004 to focus on his solo career, with the group announcing the return of Allen, Fasano and the addition of new frontman [[Jaime St. James]] the following month.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/warrant-announce-new-lineup/ |title=Warrant Announce New Lineup |website=[[Blabbermouth.net]] |date=February 15, 2004 |accessdate=July 26, 2018 }}</ref> By March, Fasano had been replaced by the returning Sweet, marking a reunion of the band's classic lineup with the exception of Lane.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/warrant-drummer-steven-sweet-rejoins-the-fold/ |title=Warrant: Drummer Steven Sweet Rejoins The Fold |website=[[Blabbermouth.net]] |date=March 17, 2004 |accessdate=July 26, 2018 }}</ref> ''[[Born Again (Warrant album)|Born Again]]'', the first Warrant album without Lane, was released in 2006.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/born-again-mw0000734589 |title=Born Again - Warrant: Songs, Reviews, Credits |last=Viglione |first=Joe |website=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=July 26, 2018 }}</ref> In early 2008, Lane returned to front Warrant for a third time.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/warrant-reunites-with-singer-jani-lane-first-photo-released/ |title=Warrant Reunites With Singer Jani Lane: First Photo Released |website=[[Blabbermouth.net]] |date=January 29, 2008 |accessdate=July 26, 2018 }}</ref> The reunion lasted less than a year, however, as Lane left for a final time in September and was replaced by former [[Lynch Mob (band)|Lynch Mob]] frontman Robert Mason.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/warrant-parts-ways-with-singer-jani-lane-again/ |title=Warrant Parts Ways With Singer Jani Lane... Again |website=[[Blabbermouth.net]] |date=September 5, 2008 |accessdate=July 26, 2018 }}</ref> Lane later died on August 11, 2011 of acute alcohol poisoning.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://loudwire.com/warrant-jani-lane-death-anniversary/ |title=Six Years Ago: Warrant Singer Jani Lane Dies |last=Wiederhorn |first=Jon |website=[[Loudwire]] |date=August 11, 2017 |accessdate=July 26, 2018 }}</ref>\n\n==Members==\n===Current===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=\"1\" width=100%\n|-\n!width=\"75\"|Image\n!width=\"120\"|Name\n!width=\"90\"|Years active\n!width=\"160\"|Instruments\n!Release contributions\n|-\n|{{CSS image crop |Image=Erik_Turner.jpg |bSize=250 |cWidth=75 |cHeight=75 |oTop=48 |oLeft=48 }}\n|[[Erik Turner]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|1984\u2013present\n|{{hlist|rhythm and lead guitars|backing vocals}}\n|rowspan=\"2\"|all [[Warrant discography|Warrant releases]]\n|-\n|\n|[[Jerry Dixon (musician)|Jerry Dixon]]\n|{{hlist|bass|backing vocals}}\n|-\n|\n|[[Steven Sweet]]\n|{{hlist|1986\u20131994|2004\u2013present}}\n|{{hlist|drums|percussion|backing vocals}}\n|rowspan=\"2\"|all Warrant releases from ''[[Dirty Rotten Filthy Stinking Rich]]'' (1989) to ''[[Dog Eat Dog (Warrant album)|Dog Eat Dog]]'' (1992), and from ''[[Born Again (Warrant album)|Born Again]]'' (2006) onwards\n|-\n|\n|[[Joey Allen]]\n|{{hlist|1987\u20131994|2004\u2013present}}\n|{{hlist|lead and rhythm guitars|backing vocals}}\n|-\n|\n|Robert Mason\n|2008\u2013present\n|{{hlist|vocals|acoustic guitar|harmonica|piano}}\n|{{hlist|''[[Rockaholic]]'' (2011)|''[[Louder Harder Faster]]'' (2017)