ty section|date=January 2011}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Toronto Argonauts}}\n{{Toronto Argonauts seasons}}\n{{1988 CFL season by team}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1988 Toronto Argonauts Season}}\n[[Category:Toronto Argonauts seasons]]\n[[Category:1988 in Toronto|Toronto Argonauts]]\n[[Category:1988 Canadian Football League season by team]]\n\n\n{{Canadianfootball-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox NFL season\n| team = Toronto Argonauts\n| year = 1988\n| record = '''14\u20134'''\n| division_place = '''1st, [[Canadian Football League East Division|East]]'''\n| coach = [[Bob O'Billovich]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.argonauts.ca/page/all-time-coaching|title=All-Time Coaching|accessdate=2011-05-07|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110422084043/http://argonauts.ca/page/all-time-coaching|archivedate=2011-04-22|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| stadium = [[Exhibition Stadium]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.argonauts.ca/page/stadium-history|title=Toronto Argonauts Stadium History|accessdate=2011-05-07|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110422083852/http://argonauts.ca/page/stadium-history|archivedate=2011-04-22|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| playoffs = '''Lost East Final'''\n| uniform = Image:CFL TOR Jersey 1985.png\n| shortnavlink = Argonauts seasons\n}}\n\nThe '''[[1988 CFL season|1988]] [[Toronto Argonauts]]''' finished in first place in the East Division with a 14\u20134 record. They appeared in the East Final. The 1988 season was the Argos' last season at [[Exhibition Stadium]], they would move into their new stadium, [[SkyDome]], the following year.\n\n==Offseason==\n{{Empty section|date=July 2010}}\n\n==Regular season==\n\n===Standings===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ '''[[CFL East Division|East Division]]'''\n! Team !! GP !! W !! L !! T !! PF !! PA !! Pts\n|- align=\"center\"\n| align=\"left\" |'''[[Toronto Argonauts]]''' || 18 || 14 || 4 || 0 || 571 || 326 || 28\n|- align=\"center\"\n| align=\"left\" |'''[[Winnipeg Blue Bombers]]''' || 18 || 9 || 9 || 0 || 407 ||